A man held over the rape of a 4-year-old girl in Hermanus at the weekend was out on parole at the time, and it is possible she might known the accused, according to police. Western Cape National Prosecuting Authority spokesperson Eric Ntabazalila said on Monday the investigating officer said the 23-year-old suspect had been out on parole for another case of attempted rape, News24 reported. Both the suspect and the child are from Mount Pleasant. The man abandoned his bail application in the Hermanus Magistrate's Court on Monday and the case was postponed to August 23 for further investigation. The child was reported missing at about 11am in Hermanus on Saturday, police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Andre Traut said. She was found bloodied four hours later and taken to hospital. She had been spotted on surveillance cameras at the Total garage next to the R43 and an employee had called the police.